Name: Anjar
Description: Anjar - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Umayyad city ruins from the 8th century with well-preserved grid layout.

Name: Baalbek
Description: Baalbek - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient Phoenician city with impressive Roman temple ruins.

Name: Byblos
Description: Byblos - UNESCO World Heritage Site. One of the oldest continuously inhabited cities in the world.

Name: Tyre
Description: Tyre - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Ancient Phoenician city with well-preserved Roman and Byzantine ruins.

Name: Ouadi Qadisha
Description: Ouadi Qadisha (the Holy Valley) and the Forest of the Cedars of God (Horsh Arz el-Rab) - UNESCO World Heritage Site. Sacred valley with ancient monasteries and cedar forest.
